\begin_layout Enumerate
Similar to class and homework, we will use a trial function 
\begin_inset Formula $\psi_{k}(y)=e^{-\alpha|y|}$
\end_inset

 in the limit of small 
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha>0$
\end_inset

.
 We need to show 
\begin_inset Formula $\frac{\langle\psi,\hat{H}\psi\rangle}{\langle\psi,\psi\rangle}<k^{2}$
\end_inset

, i.e.
 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\alpha+\frac{k^{2}}{\alpha}+\int_{-\infty}^{\infty}Ve^{-2\alpha|y|}dy=\int_{-\infty}^{\infty}\left(\alpha^{2}+k^{2}+V\right)e^{-2\alpha|y|}dy=\boxed{\langle\psi_{k},\hat{H}_{k}\psi_{k}\rangle<k^{2}\langle\psi_{k},\psi_{k}\rangle}=k^{2}\int_{-\infty}^{\infty}e^{-2\alpha|y|}dy=\frac{k^{2}}{\alpha}.
\]

\end_inset

Cancelling the 
\begin_inset Formula $k^{2}/\alpha$
\end_inset

 terms, we obtain the condition 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\alpha+\int_{-\infty}^{\infty}Ve^{-2\alpha|y|}dy<0
\]

\end_inset

for some 
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha>0$
\end_inset

.
 It suffices, therefore, to show that the left-hand side is negative for
 
\begin_inset Formula $\lim_{\alpha\to0^{+}}$
\end_inset

.
 Since 
\begin_inset Formula $\left|Ve^{-2\alpha|y|}\right|\le|V|$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\int|V|<\infty$
\end_inset

 by assumption, we can use the dominated convergence theorem to interchange
 the limit and the integral.
 The limit of the left-hand-side is therefore 
\begin_inset Formula $0+\int V$
\end_inset

, which is 
\begin_inset Formula $<0$
\end_inset

 by assumption.
 It follows that we have at least one eigenvalue below the light cone, i.e.
 a guided mode for all 
\begin_inset Formula $k$
\end_inset

.
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

(The problem only asked you to prove it for 
\begin_inset Formula $k\neq0$
\end_inset

, since in the Maxwell case you don't have guided modes at 
\begin_inset Formula $k=0$
\end_inset

, but in the Schrödinger case we have a guided mode at all 
\begin_inset Formula $k$
\end_inset

